title: USGS Landsat 5 Level 2, Collection 2, Tier 1
description:
This dataset contains atmospherically corrected
surface reflectance and land surface temperature derived from the data
produced by the Landsat TM sensor.
These images contain 4 visible and near-infrared (VNIR) bands and
2 short-wave infrared (SWIR) bands processed to orthorectified surface
reflectance, and one thermal infrared (TIR) band processed to orthorectified
surface temperature. They also contain intermediate bands used in
calculation of the ST products, as well as QA bands.

Landsat 4 and 5 SR products are created with the Landsat Ecosystem Disturbance
Adaptive Processing System (LEDAPS) algorithm (version 3.4.0).
All Collection 2 ST products are created with a single-channel algorithm
jointly created by the Rochester Institute of Technology (RIT) and
National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA)
Jet Propulsion Laboratory (JPL).

Strips of collected data are packaged into overlapping \"scenes\" covering approximately
170km x 183km using a [standardized reference grid](https://landsat.gsfc.nasa.gov/about/worldwide-reference-system).

Some assets have only SR data, in which case ST bands are present but empty.
For assets with both ST and SR bands, 'PROCESSING_LEVEL' is set to 'L2SP'.
For assets with only SR bands, 'PROCESSING_LEVEL' is set to 'L2SR'.

[Additional documentation and usage examples.](/earth-engine/guides/landsat)

Data provider notes:

* Data products must contain both optical and thermal data to be
  successfully processed to surface temperature, as ASTER NDVI is
  required to temporally adjust the ASTER GED product to the target Landsat
  scene. Therefore, night time acquisitions cannot be processed to
  surface temperature.

* A known error exists in the surface temperature retrievals relative
  to clouds and possibly cloud shadows. The characterization of these
  issues has been documented by
  [Cook et al., (2014)](https://doi.org/10.3390/rs61111244).

eo:bands.description:
A general interpretation of atmospheric opacity
generated by LEDAPS and based on the radiance viewed over Dark Dense
Vegetation (DDV) within the scene. A general interpretation of atmospheric
opacity is that values (after scaling by 0.001 is applied)
less than 0.1 are clear, 0.1-0.3 are average,
and values greater than 0.3 indicate haze or other cloud situations.
SR values from pixels with high atmospheric opacity will be less reliable,
especially under high solar zenith angle conditions. The
SR_ATMOS_OPACITY band is provided for advanced users and for product quality
assessment and has not been validated. Most users are advised to instead use
the QA_PIXEL band information for cloud discrimination.
eo:bands.name: SR_ATMOS_OPACITY

eo:bands.description:
Band 6 surface temperature.
If 'PROCESSING_LEVEL' is set to 'L2SR', this band is fully masked out.
eo:bands.name: ST_B6

eo:bands.description:
Atmospheric Transmittance.
If 'PROCESSING_LEVEL' is set to 'L2SR', this band is fully masked out.
eo:bands.name: ST_ATRAN

eo:bands.description:
Pixel distance to cloud.
If 'PROCESSING_LEVEL' is set to 'L2SR', this band is fully masked out.
eo:bands.name: ST_CDIST

eo:bands.description:
Downwelled Radiance.
If 'PROCESSING_LEVEL' is set to 'L2SR', this band is fully masked out.
eo:bands.name: ST_DRAD

eo:bands.description:
Emissivity estimated from ASTER GED.
If 'PROCESSING_LEVEL' is set to 'L2SR', this band is fully masked out.
eo:bands.name: ST_EMIS

eo:bands.description:
Emissivity standard deviation.
If 'PROCESSING_LEVEL' is set to 'L2SR', this band is fully masked out.
eo:bands.name: ST_EMSD

eo:bands.description:
Uncertainty of the Surface Temperature band.
If 'PROCESSING_LEVEL' is set to 'L2SR', this band is fully masked out.
eo:bands.name: ST_QA

eo:bands.description:
Thermal band converted to radiance.
If 'PROCESSING_LEVEL' is set to 'L2SR', this band is fully masked out.
eo:bands.name: ST_TRAD

eo:bands.description:
Upwelled Radiance.
If 'PROCESSING_LEVEL' is set to 'L2SR', this band is fully masked out.
eo:bands.name: ST_URAD

gee:schema.description: Name and version of the surface reflectance algorithm.
gee:schema.name: ALGORITHM_SOURCE_SURFACE_REFLECTANCE

gee:schema.description: Name and version of the surface temperature algorithm.
gee:schema.name: ALGORITHM_SOURCE_SURFACE_TEMPERATURE

gee:schema.description: Percentage cloud cover (0-100), -1 = not calculated.
gee:schema.name: CLOUD_COVER

gee:schema.description: Percentage cloud cover over land (0-100), -1 = not calculated.
gee:schema.name: CLOUD_COVER_LAND

gee:schema.description: Scene collection category, "T1" or "T2".
gee:schema.name: COLLECTION_CATEGORY

gee:schema.description: Air temperature data source.
gee:schema.name: DATA_SOURCE_AIR_TEMPERATURE

gee:schema.description: Elevation data source.
gee:schema.name: DATA_SOURCE_ELEVATION

gee:schema.description: Ozone data source.
gee:schema.name: DATA_SOURCE_OZONE

gee:schema.description: Pressure data source.
gee:schema.name: DATA_SOURCE_PRESSURE

gee:schema.description: Reanalysis data source.
gee:schema.name: DATA_SOURCE_REANALYSIS

gee:schema.description: Water vapor data source.
gee:schema.name: DATA_SOURCE_WATER_VAPOR

gee:schema.description: Timestamp of the date when the product was generated.
gee:schema.name: DATE_PRODUCT_GENERATED

gee:schema.description: Earth-Sun distance (AU).
gee:schema.name: EARTH_SUN_DISTANCE

gee:schema.description:
Identifier to inform the user of the orbital ephemeris type used:
"DEFINITIVE" or "PREDICTIVE". If the field is not present, the user should
assume "PREDICTIVE".
gee:schema.name: EPHEMERIS_TYPE

gee:schema.description:
Combined RMSE (Root Mean Square Error) of the geometric
residuals (meters) in both across-track and along-track
directions. This parameter is only present if the L1_PROCESSING_LEVEL
is L1TP.
gee:schema.name: GEOMETRIC_RMSE_MODEL

gee:schema.description:
RMSE (Root Mean Square Error) of the geometric residuals (meters)
measured on the GCPs (Ground Control Points) used in geometric
precision correction in the across-track direction. This parameter is
only present if the L1_PROCESSING_LEVEL is L1TP.
gee:schema.name: GEOMETRIC_RMSE_MODEL_X

gee:schema.description:
RMSE (Root Mean Square Error) of the geometric residuals (meters)
measured on the GCPs (Ground Control Points) used in geometric
precision correction in the along-track direction. This parameter is
only present if the L1_PROCESSING_LEVEL is L1TP.
gee:schema.name: GEOMETRIC_RMSE_MODEL_Y

gee:schema.description:
Number of GCPs used in the precision correction process.
This parameter is only present if the L1_PROCESSING_LEVEL is L1TP.
gee:schema.name: GROUND_CONTROL_POINTS_MODEL

gee:schema.description:
GCP dataset version used in the precision correction process. This
parameter is only present if the L1_PROCESSING_LEVEL is L1TP.
gee:schema.name: GROUND_CONTROL_POINTS_VERSION

gee:schema.description:
Composite image quality for the bands.
0 = worst, 9 = best, -1 = quality not calculated or assessed.
gee:schema.name: IMAGE_QUALITY

gee:schema.description: Product generation date for the corresponding L1 product.
gee:schema.name: L1_DATE_PRODUCT_GENERATED

gee:schema.description: Landsat Product Identifier for the corresponding L1 product.
gee:schema.name: L1_LANDSAT_PRODUCT_ID

gee:schema.description: Processing Level for the corresponding L1 product.
gee:schema.name: L1_PROCESSING_LEVEL

gee:schema.description: Processing software version for the corresponding L1 product.
gee:schema.name: L1_PROCESSING_SOFTWARE_VERSION

gee:schema.description: Landsat Product Identifier
gee:schema.name: LANDSAT_PRODUCT_ID

gee:schema.description: Short Landsat Scene Identifier
gee:schema.name: LANDSAT_SCENE_ID

gee:schema.description:
"L2SP" when both SR and LST bands are present, or "L2SR" when only
SR bands are present.
gee:schema.name: PROCESSING_LEVEL

gee:schema.description: The processing software version that created the product.
gee:schema.name: PROCESSING_SOFTWARE_VERSION

gee:schema.description: Time of the observations as in ISO 8601 string.
gee:schema.name: SCENE_CENTER_TIME

gee:schema.description: Name of the sensor.
gee:schema.name: SENSOR_ID

gee:schema.description: Name of the spacecraft.
gee:schema.name: SPACECRAFT_ID

gee:schema.description:
Sun azimuth angle in degrees for the image center location at the
image center acquisition time. A positive value indicates angles to the
east or clockwise from the north. A negative value indicates angles to
the west or counterclockwise from the north.
gee:schema.name: SUN_AZIMUTH

gee:schema.description:
Sun elevation angle in degrees for the image center location at the
image center acquisition time. A positive value indicates a daytime
scene. A negative value indicates a nighttime scene.
Note: For reflectance calculation, the sun zenith angle is needed,
which is 90 - sun elevation angle.
gee:schema.name: SUN_ELEVATION

gee:schema.description: Maximum achievable temperature value for Band 6.
gee:schema.name: TEMPERATURE_MAXIMUM_BAND_ST_B6

gee:schema.description: Minimum achievable temperature value for Band 6.
gee:schema.name: TEMPERATURE_MINIMUM_BAND_ST_B6

gee:schema.description: WRS path number of scene.
gee:schema.name: WRS_PATH

gee:schema.description: WRS row number of scene.
gee:schema.name: WRS_ROW

and therefore reside in the public domain and may be used, transferred, or reproduced without copyright restriction.

Acknowledgement or credit of the USGS as data source should be provided
by including a line of text citation such as the example shown below.

(Product, Image, Photograph, or Dataset Name) courtesy of
the U.S. Geological Survey

Example: Landsat-7 image courtesy of the U.S. Geological Survey

See the
[USGS Visual Identity System Guidance](https://www.usgs.gov/information-policies-and-instructions/usgs-visual-identity-system)
